# fire-planner Visual QA

Before considering UI work done, review the changed screens as a user would:

- Check visual hierarchy: the main action/result should be obvious, secondary controls should not compete, and dense financial tables should remain scannable.
- Check spacing rhythm: section gaps, card padding, inline control gaps, and table cell padding should feel intentional rather than mechanically uniform.
- Check alignment: card edges, headings, controls, tables, and chart panels should line up across the page where reasonable.
- Check copy hierarchy: labels, helper text, warnings, and disclaimers should use consistent sizes and weights.
- Check light and dark mode: no low-contrast text, invisible borders, harsh pure-black/pure-white fields, or chart colors that disappear.
- Check responsive breakpoints: mobile wrapping, tablet tab bars, wide desktop max widths, and horizontal scrolling for data-heavy tables/charts.
- Check accessible states: keyboard focus is visible, active tabs/modes are announced, and disabled controls remain understandable.

When UI changes are broad, prefer a quick browser pass after tests: run the app, inspect at least the default basic view, advanced view, compare/methodology navigation if touched, and both themes when dark mode is involved.
